&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Overview:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;JAN-PRO is seeking a Senior Vice President of Marketing to own and advance the marketing strategy for one of the leading commercial cleaning franchise brands in the market. This role will be responsible for driving brand-level marketing strategy (franchise and company-owned), strengthening Regional Developer engagement, increasing adoption of marketing best practices and technology, and ensuring marketing is viewed as a trusted, value-creating partner to the JAN-PRO system.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate is a strategic, commercially minded marketing leader with deep franchise experience, strong relationship-building skills, and a proven ability to translate enterprise marketing strategy into practical, field-adopted execution. This person must be comfortable operating at both the strategic and regional level, partnering closely with brand leadership, Regional Developers, franchise business coaches, sales, and other cross-functional stakeholders to improve marketing performance, sentiment, adoption, and growth outcomes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Brand Marketing Strategy&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with brand leadership, sales, operations, Regional Developers, and shared services teams to develop and execute marketing strategies that support JAN-PRO’s growth goals across the organization, including lead generation, local market activation, customer acquisition, retention support, and franchise system adoption.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate and communicate business priorities, growth goals, and Regional Developer needs into clear marketing plans, priorities, and execution roadmaps.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own and manage JAN-PRO’s agency partners and vendor relationships, ensuring partners are aligned to brand priorities, performance expectations, sharing of insights, budget discipline, Regional Developer needs, and measurable business outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the senior marketing voice for JAN-PRO, ensuring strategy is commercially grounded, locally relevant, and aligned to the realities of the commercial cleaning category.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify opportunities to strengthen brand positioning, market relevance, lead generation, local market activation, customer retention support, and Regional Developer enablement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with digital, creative, operations, sales, and analytics teams to ensure JAN-PRO marketing efforts are coordinated, measurable, and actionable.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Regional Developer Relations &amp;amp; Communications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build strong, trusted relationships with JAN-PRO Regional Developers and serve as a key marketing partner to the regional network.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create consistent communication rhythms that increase transparency, confidence, and understanding of marketing priorities, performance, initiatives, and available resources.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Gather feedback from Regional Developers and translate system needs into clear marketing opportunities, recommendations, and action plans.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively identify gaps in Regional Developer sentiment, adoption, or understanding and develop strategies to address them.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Represent marketing in Regional Developer meetings, councils, forums, webinars, and planning conversations as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Marketing Adoption &amp;amp; Enablement&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive adoption of JAN-PRO marketing best practices, tools, campaigns, playbooks, and technology across the Regional Developer network.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with the operations team to create practical training, too

&lt;div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Overview:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Senior FP&amp;amp;A Analyst will partner with key operational leaders to provide valuable insights into how the business is performing while also identifying and understanding the underlying key drivers of performance. This role will also assess areas of growth opportunity and improvement through meaningful analyses that help articulate the story behind how operations and sales can drive business performance.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Core Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with general accounting team to facilitate the month end close process&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review monthly financials to understand variances to forecast and budget and articulate those findings to executive leadership and business partners&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop annual budgets and rolling forecasts through the use of complex financial models, software systems, and insights from business partners and leadership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leverage accounting and financial systems to gather, analyze and interpret ambiguous or large sets of data&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with other members of the finance team to drive financial reporting each month to articulate the financial performance of the businessclearly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with the creation of key financial presentations to senior leadership (i.e. quarterly board meetings)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support Treasury on cash positioning and strategies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide insights into the status of Accounts Receivable to enable operational and sales teams to effectively complete the order to cash cycle&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support implementation of new accounting, accounts payable, expense processing and other related financial systems to gain further operational efficiencies &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Critical Skills &amp;amp; Attributes:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication and interpersonal skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attention to detail and emphasis on accuracyand quality&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Time management skills along with ability to meet deadlines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Microsoft Office Suite (Excel, Outlook, PowerPoint, Word)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NetSuite, SAP Concur, Airbase, Expensify or similar software experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good fit with Empower Brands’ core values, including championing the success of franchisees, Go-Getters, Disciplined, and People First.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated strong work ethic and results focus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Experience &amp;amp; Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s Degree in economics, finance or other business related area&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2-5 years at a leading investment bank and/ or private equity firm who seeks operating experience with a high-performance team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
